I actually went to search for which is the more proper term. My own feeling was that she-wolf is a more furshit oriented term (not that /hmofa/ isn't some flavor of furshit) so I'm not one for using it.
After some light googling though, it seems that "she-wolf" has actual professional and historical usage. For example, she-wolf refers to female grey wolves, as well as referring very specifically to the wolf that mothered Romulus and Remus (you know, the founders of Rome).
Meanwhile the only things that came up for "wolfess" includes this definition, some furry pictures, several deviant-art profiles, and a seven chapter long Legend of Zelda fanfiction.

tl;dr she-wolf is the more professional term over the two while wolfess isn't much of a word at all. It's even setting off Chrome's spell checker.
